	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: increment hex bytes with mouse wheel</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />ResEdit was before mice made by Apple even routinely had a second button, let alone a scroll wheel. That didn't become common until the <s>Mighty</s> Mouse. Does its successor (Interface Builder in Xcode) bind any editing functions to the wheel?<br /><br />How would a hex editor distinguish scroll wheel events to change a nibble from scroll wheel events to actually scroll the window? Would it be acceptable to hold a key on the keyboard to enter wheel=increment mode? If you cannot find an existing hex editor as precedent to answer the question of user expectation, do tracker-style music sequencers have a similar binding for the scroll wheel?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


